# Supabase + Directus Rules

## Supabase

- **Always use Supabase CLI** for all DB operations — never direct SQL in production without a migration.
- Local dev: `supabase start` → API at `http://127.0.0.1:54321`, DB at `postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:54322/postgres`, Studio at `http://127.0.0.1:54323`.
- Create migrations: `supabase migration new <descriptive-name>`.
- **Local day-to-day:** `supabase migration up` or `scripts/dev-db-migrate.sh` / `dev-db-migrate.ps1` — applies pending migrations **without** wiping Postgres (Directus survives).
- **Local full replay (rare):** `supabase db reset` — then run `scripts/dev-db-reset.*` so Directus is repaired.
- **Hosted:** `supabase db push`.
- Never skip `supabase db diff` before pushing to verify migration.
- RLS on every table that is user-reachable via the Data API (anon/publishable key).
- `service_role` key backend-only. Never in client bundles.
- Use Supabase MCP for introspection: `plugin-supabase-supabase`.

## Schema Conventions

```sql
-- All PKs: uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
-- All timestamps: timestamptz DEFAULT now()
-- Soft delete: deleted_at timestamptz (prefer over hard delete)
-- Slugs: text UNIQUE NOT NULL (for URL routing)
-- JSONB metadata: DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb
-- Enums: CREATE TYPE ... AS ENUM (...) before tables that use them
```

## Official Hierarchy

Every elected official, judge, or candidate maps to this hierarchy:

```
jurisdiction_level: federal | state | county | city | district
office_type: senator | representative | governor | lt_governor | attorney_general |
             mayor | city_council | county_commissioner | county_clerk | county_mayor |
             state_supreme_justice | state_appellate_judge | state_district_judge | federal_judge
```

Judges: `party = NULL` (non-partisan). Track `retention_year`, `is_current`.
Non-election years: `is_current = true` officials are displayed even if non-GOP.
Election years: include challengers/candidates via `races` + `candidates` (existing schema).

## Directus

- Connects to the SAME Supabase Postgres. No separate DB.
- Local dev: Directus metadata often lives in `public` alongside app tables; that is fine unless it causes real problems. Prefer not forcing `DB_SCHEMA` unless you have verified bootstrap.
- Schema owned by Supabase migrations for app tables. Directus reads/introspects; use `cms/scripts/register-app-collections.ps1` (or schema snapshot) so app tables appear under **Content**.
- Scaffold: `bunx create-directus-project@latest cms` OR Docker compose (preferred for self-hosted).
- Extensions: `npx create-directus-extension@latest` (only allowed `npx`).
- Extensions live in `cms/extensions/` as **flat** directories (`cms/extensions/<name>/package.json`). Directus does not load `cms/extensions/hooks/<name>` style nesting; each extension must be a direct child of the extensions root.
- One concern per extension, ~200 LOC.
- Custom interfaces/panels must use design system CSS vars + Lucide icons.
- Flows: use for "on item save → trigger LLM correlation/refresh" (POST to backend worker API).

## Migration Naming

```
YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_<descriptive_name>.sql
20260319180000_races_candidates.sql    ← existing
20260419000000_jurisdiction_officials.sql
20260419000001_directus_role_grants.sql
```
